        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 7:20AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 720 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of West Columbia, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Rosenberg, Lake Jackson, Bay City, Freeport, El Campo,
Clute, Wharton, Palacios, West Columbia, Sweeny, South Texas Nuclear
Plant, Richwood, Brazoria, Needville, Jones Creek, Holiday Lakes,
Pleak, Fairchilds, Bailey's Prairie, and Sargent.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
